Chicago Bulls Shot Brief

Isaac Dhyanchand

2025-11-03

Chicago Bulls Shot Profile (20142024)

Key Findings

  • Most efficient scoring comes from the restricted area and above-the-break threes.
  • Mid-range shots continue to yield the lowest efficiency across seasons.
  • The shot profile has remained steady, rim and 3-point attempts dominate.
  • Top-of-the-key three-point attempts increased slightly after 2018.
  • Corner threes are limited, suggesting a potential area for growth.
  • Paint and rim efficiency remain consistent year to year (~6065% FG).

Figure 1 Season-by-season shot chart animation (Bulls, 20142024)

Findings from Figure 1

  • Shot selection hasnt changed much
  • In 2020, visibly fewer mid-range shots were taken
  • Most three point shots are generally made from top of the key

Figure 2. Bulls Zone Efficiency and Distribution of Shots

Findings from Figure 2.

  • We can see a slight decrease in the mid-range shots volume from 2022-2024.
  • Overall shot distribution and percentages have remained relatively the same over the last 3 years.
  • Corner threes show solid efficiency but limited usage compared to other zones. -Visual emphasis shows clear focus on rim attempts and top-of-the-key three pointers.

Figure 3. Field-goal percentage by zone and season

Findings from Figure 3.

  • Highest percentage shots came from the Restricted Area.
  • Midrange and in the paint percentages have increased fairly consistently since 2021.
  • Three point percentages have not changed much over time.

Figure 4. Shot Attempts by Zone Over Time

Findings from Figure 4.

  • There is a fairly constant increase in the amount of three-point shots attempted.
  • Mid-range shots seemed to have generally decreased since 2014.
  • Restricted Area shots have consistently had the most volume in each year.
  • Corner threes are not popular shots

Summary Takeaways

  • Shot efficiency remained stable across the past decade, with most value coming from the restricted area and above the break threes.
  • Three-point attmept share has grown modestly, reflecting modern offensive changes.
  • Defensive emphasis should focus on rim protection and limiting above the break threes.
